  "text": "In recent years, many researchers have attempted to improve microalgal lipid yields using different techniques including genetic engineering of important enzymes (such as acetyl-CoA carboxylase) of the lipid metabolism. Reports from the National Renewable Energy Laboratory in the USA indicate that the lipid contents of engineered microalgae were increased up to 60% and 40%, respectively, in laboratory and outdoor cultivations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Besides the genetic techniques, the application of small bioactive molecules (such as ACh) offers an additional approach for the manipulation of microalgal biomass, lipid content, and fatty acid composition, as confirmed by this study.",
